1
00:00:00,056 --> 00:00:01,356
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,356 --> 00:00:02,556
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,475 --> 00:00:06,008
(Episode 56)

4
00:00:10,593 --> 00:00:11,593
Team Manager.

5
00:00:13,004 --> 00:00:14,004
I don't think...

6
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,605
I can do this anymore.

7
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:20,747
No matter how hard I try to stop it...

8
00:00:22,672 --> 00:00:24,139
No matter how hard I try
to hold it back...

9
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:33,433
I don't think I can anymore.

10
00:01:31,694 --> 00:01:32,761
I'm sorry...

11
00:01:33,743 --> 00:01:35,243
for hurting you all this time.

12
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,920
Why did you change your mind?

13
00:01:39,228 --> 00:01:40,784
You said you were heading down a road...

14
00:01:41,164 --> 00:01:42,664
with an obvious ending.

15
00:01:44,186 --> 00:01:45,925
You said no one knows the ending.

16
00:01:46,915 --> 00:01:49,615
So I decided to be brave for once.

17
00:01:51,042 --> 00:01:52,309
If I'm with you, Eun Ae,

18
00:01:53,713 --> 00:01:54,819
I feel like I could somehow...

19
00:01:55,361 --> 00:01:56,693
become warmer...

20
00:01:57,572 --> 00:01:58,867
and happier.

21
00:02:09,192 --> 00:02:10,595
Good grief.

22
00:02:10,914 --> 00:02:12,283
You're going to wear that photo out.

23
00:02:13,229 --> 00:02:14,329
Aren't you going to sleep?

24
00:02:16,157 --> 00:02:17,317
I was thinking about Gyeol.

25
00:02:18,078 --> 00:02:20,978
I didn't even know
the kid could smile this brightly.

26
00:02:21,487 --> 00:02:22,687
It's fascinating.

27
00:02:23,064 --> 00:02:24,064
I know.

28
00:02:24,493 --> 00:02:27,726
I never knew he could laugh...

29
00:02:28,311 --> 00:02:29,715
and chat like that either.

30
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:34,327
I think he's found the right person.

31
00:02:35,389 --> 00:02:36,552
What do you mean?

32
00:02:36,933 --> 00:02:39,989
Well, I practically forced him
to repay a debt before I die,

33
00:02:39,989 --> 00:02:42,107
so he's only staying because of that.

34
00:02:43,581 --> 00:02:46,731
But somehow, I get the feeling
he might not leave after all.

35
00:02:47,128 --> 00:02:48,128
What?

36
00:02:48,414 --> 00:02:50,963
Do you think
Gyeol will actually settle down here?

37
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:56,440
Even if they like each other,
that's a different matter.

38
00:02:57,173 --> 00:02:58,600
Then we should make sure it happens.

39
00:02:59,333 --> 00:03:00,700
We should pick a day...

40
00:03:01,229 --> 00:03:04,000
and properly invite Eun Ae over.

41
00:03:04,526 --> 00:03:05,526
To the house?

42
00:03:05,855 --> 00:03:09,227
Somehow, I felt like...

43
00:03:10,852 --> 00:03:13,752
I could stop being a coward and be brave.

44
00:03:19,935 --> 00:03:20,968
Maybe it's because of this.

45
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,389
I was like that too.

46
00:03:25,643 --> 00:03:27,315
Whenever I was tired and worn out,

47
00:03:27,773 --> 00:03:29,661
or scared and lacking courage,

48
00:03:31,063 --> 00:03:33,221
I'd look at that clover.

49
00:03:33,221 --> 00:03:35,696
It gave me strength and courage.

50
00:03:39,033 --> 00:03:40,368
This playground...

51
00:03:41,144 --> 00:03:43,044
is a really special place to me.

52
00:03:44,831 --> 00:03:45,831
Why?

53
00:03:46,152 --> 00:03:47,984
Because it's where you first met
your first love?

54
00:03:51,665 --> 00:03:53,781
My mom had something come up that day,

55
00:03:54,862 --> 00:03:58,029
and she accidentally left me here
and forgot about me.

56
00:03:59,847 --> 00:04:02,576
Thanks to the lucky flag
you gave me back then,

57
00:04:03,071 --> 00:04:06,271
I found the courage to make it home.

58
00:04:07,781 --> 00:04:09,681
Otherwise,

59
00:04:10,973 --> 00:04:12,576
I might've become a lost child that day.

60
00:04:14,273 --> 00:04:16,800
That must've been...

61
00:04:17,933 --> 00:04:19,500
a really difficult day for you too.

62
00:04:21,708 --> 00:04:24,375
Was it a difficult day for you too?

63
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,633
It was your birthday.

64
00:04:28,696 --> 00:04:29,796
It's a special day.

65
00:04:31,651 --> 00:04:35,168
A very special day for me.

66
00:04:38,552 --> 00:04:41,803
This is also where I first met
your grandmother.

67
00:04:42,359 --> 00:04:46,059
She collapsed from low blood pressure
right on this bench.

68
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:48,700
That's when I installed Joy for her too.

69
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:51,400
You met her here?

70
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:54,100
Why was Grandma here?

71
00:04:54,529 --> 00:04:55,529
Good question.

72
00:04:55,808 --> 00:04:57,975
This is pretty far from your house.

73
00:04:58,700 --> 00:05:02,896
At this point, I don't think
this playground is special only to me.

74
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:05,967
It's special to both of us.

75
00:05:05,967 --> 00:05:06,967
You're right.

76
00:05:07,888 --> 00:05:11,243
If we hadn't met again here,

77
00:05:12,693 --> 00:05:13,693
we might've...

78
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:17,000
never recognized each other.

79
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:21,568
It's getting late.

80
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,600
Should we head home?

81
00:05:24,352 --> 00:05:25,352
Wait.

82
00:05:26,845 --> 00:05:27,845
Then...

83
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:32,093
Is today our first day together?

84
00:05:33,731 --> 00:05:34,831
No.

85
00:05:35,881 --> 00:05:38,800
It's been 25 years and one month.
That's 9,156 days.

86
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:49,299
All right. Let's make today Day One.

87
00:05:57,876 --> 00:05:58,876
Thank you...

88
00:06:00,097 --> 00:06:03,497
for accepting me
instead of pushing me away.

89
00:06:04,744 --> 00:06:05,744
Me too.

90
00:06:07,579 --> 00:06:09,579
Thank you for bravely taking my hand.

91
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:12,740
Thank you, Team Manager.

92
00:06:28,633 --> 00:06:30,379
Here, eat.

93
00:06:31,124 --> 00:06:34,200
Mother, Father should have it first.

94
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:35,200
Stop!

95
00:06:35,633 --> 00:06:38,181
This is your first drumstick
from your mother-in-law.

96
00:06:38,533 --> 00:06:40,633
Don't you know they slaughter a prized hen
when the son-in-law visits?

97
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:43,300
I didn't actually slaughter one myself,

98
00:06:43,509 --> 00:06:44,709
but hurry and eat.

99
00:06:45,172 --> 00:06:48,105
I really don't know
what to do with myself.

100
00:06:48,523 --> 00:06:50,723
That's enough. Chief Ko is uncomfortable.

101
00:06:51,684 --> 00:06:53,304
Son, are you uncomfortable?

102
00:06:53,616 --> 00:06:55,116
Sorry? Son?

103
00:06:55,504 --> 00:06:57,413
No, not at all.

104
00:06:58,316 --> 00:06:59,733
I'm very comfortable.

105
00:07:00,479 --> 00:07:01,479
- Thank you for the meal.
- Good.

106
00:07:02,629 --> 00:07:03,729
Looks good.

107
00:07:08,517 --> 00:07:11,341
Mother, your braised chicken
is the best in the universe.

108
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:12,700
Really?

109
00:07:13,636 --> 00:07:14,636
Father,

110
00:07:15,735 --> 00:07:16,935
let me pour you a drink.

111
00:07:18,533 --> 00:07:20,733
Don't go throwing around "Father"
so casually.

112
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:25,272
Yes, Mr. Seo. My apologies.

113
00:07:26,206 --> 00:07:28,431
I'm pretty sure I told you...

114
00:07:28,431 --> 00:07:30,331
everything has its proper steps.

115
00:07:32,589 --> 00:07:34,251
So after that public proposal,

116
00:07:34,533 --> 00:07:35,976
what exactly did you gain?

117
00:07:36,565 --> 00:07:38,179
It's not that I was trying
to gain anything.

118
00:07:38,777 --> 00:07:41,075
All I could think about
was stopping Seung Ri from leaving.

119
00:07:41,590 --> 00:07:43,190
If I took things step by step
and she left to study abroad,

120
00:07:43,546 --> 00:07:45,675
I'd have no chance at all.

121
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:49,437
Pour me one too.

122
00:07:50,471 --> 00:07:51,471
Yes, Mother.

123
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,160
Don't worry.

124
00:07:57,669 --> 00:08:01,133
If Gyeol won't budge,
Seung Ri doesn't stand a chance.

125
00:08:01,677 --> 00:08:03,100
In the end, you'll be the winner.

126
00:08:03,471 --> 00:08:06,071
Come on.
A toast with my future son-in-law.

127
00:08:06,933 --> 00:08:08,331
- Thank you.
- Cheers.

128
00:08:10,684 --> 00:08:11,784
I'm home.

129
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:15,037
Seung Ri's back.

130
00:08:18,426 --> 00:08:19,426
Goodness.

131
00:08:19,753 --> 00:08:21,886
Where else are you going to
find a man like him?

132
00:08:22,621 --> 00:08:23,952
Welcome home. You must be hungry.

133
00:08:24,852 --> 00:08:25,919
Chief.

134
00:08:26,201 --> 00:08:28,632
Mother made braised chicken.
Come in and eat with us.

135
00:08:29,268 --> 00:08:30,941
Should I leave,

136
00:08:30,941 --> 00:08:32,262
or would you rather leave, Chief?

137
00:08:32,262 --> 00:08:33,262
Seo Seung Ri.

138
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:35,704
No matter how close you are with Chief Ko,
mind your manners.

139
00:08:36,060 --> 00:08:37,060
Dad.

140
00:08:37,060 --> 00:08:38,176
It's okay, Mr. Seo.

141
00:08:38,623 --> 00:08:41,515
Seung Ri hasn't done anything wrong to me,
so please don't scold her too much.

142
00:08:44,064 --> 00:08:45,709
I completely lost track of time.

143
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:49,877
What are you talking about?
We just started eating.

144
00:08:50,145 --> 00:08:51,145
Come in, Son.

145
00:08:51,743 --> 00:08:52,743
You too!

146
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,100
Mom.

147
00:08:55,303 --> 00:08:56,303
It's all right, Mother.

148
00:08:56,741 --> 00:08:57,841
I've eaten plenty.

149
00:08:58,331 --> 00:08:59,768
Then I'll get going.

150
00:09:00,533 --> 00:09:01,533
All right.

151
00:09:02,391 --> 00:09:04,040
- Have a good night.
- Okay.

152
00:09:09,757 --> 00:09:11,857
If you let a man like that get away,

153
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:14,379
you'll regret it
for the rest of your life.

154
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:18,433
Eat first.

155
00:09:19,152 --> 00:09:20,331
We'll talk about Chief Ko later.

156
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:27,869
Seung Ri, I ran into Min Ho at the door.

157
00:09:28,359 --> 00:09:29,359
And...

158
00:09:30,988 --> 00:09:32,787
Poor sister.

159
00:09:33,847 --> 00:09:35,821
Mom, I'm not eating.

160
00:09:36,204 --> 00:09:37,389
Up to you.

161
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,123
Why are you in here?

162
00:09:54,914 --> 00:09:56,560
I wanted some advice.

163
00:09:56,904 --> 00:09:57,904
But...

164
00:09:58,827 --> 00:10:01,576
this doesn't seem like the right mood,
so I'm just sitting here.

165
00:10:01,745 --> 00:10:02,845
Then get out.

166
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:05,883
What I'm about to say
isn't directed at you.

167
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:07,933
I'm just venting.

168
00:10:09,420 --> 00:10:12,987
There was someone
I absolutely couldn't stand.

169
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:16,891
Seriously, every time we met,
it was like meeting my worst enemy.

170
00:10:17,902 --> 00:10:19,648
She had a terrible personality.

171
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,672
And she was exactly
my least favorite type.

172
00:10:21,672 --> 00:10:24,101
On top of that,
she was a walking fashion disaster.

173
00:10:25,743 --> 00:10:26,743
But...

174
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:29,016
For some reason,

175
00:10:29,463 --> 00:10:30,496
all of a sudden,

176
00:10:32,456 --> 00:10:34,016
she seems so pretty.

177
00:10:34,661 --> 00:10:37,032
She's not even my type. But she's pretty.

178
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:41,685
Have I been single for too long?

179
00:10:42,961 --> 00:10:45,194
I think I'm losing my mind.
I should probably see a doctor, right?

180
00:10:51,609 --> 00:10:52,609
Here we go again.

181
00:10:53,386 --> 00:10:54,837
Seo Seung Ri's crazy dance time.

182
00:11:01,563 --> 00:11:03,091
What are you doing?

183
00:11:03,460 --> 00:11:04,725
Dance with me.

184
00:11:05,233 --> 00:11:07,065
Tonight, let's just go...

185
00:11:07,065 --> 00:11:09,032
completely crazy together. Okay?

186
00:11:29,180 --> 00:11:30,180
What...

187
00:11:39,297 --> 00:11:41,297
Those two...

188
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:43,136
Have they both lost their minds?

189
00:11:44,533 --> 00:11:47,340
A toast to your beautiful hair,

190
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:49,740
which you sacrificed
for the sake of the truth.

191
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:51,500
Cheers.

192
00:11:51,952 --> 00:11:54,171
A toast to your precious nose,

193
00:11:54,384 --> 00:11:56,821
which narrowly escaped being stolen.
Cheers.

194
00:11:58,944 --> 00:12:00,941
A toast to your deep
and crystal-clear presbyopia.

195
00:12:01,823 --> 00:12:02,823
Cheers.

196
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:04,333
What? A toast to my presbyopia?

197
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:07,033
Not to my sparkling eyes?

198
00:12:07,433 --> 00:12:09,833
Well, your eyes do sparkle.

199
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:11,557
But because of presbyopia,

200
00:12:11,793 --> 00:12:14,393
you mistook Kang Yeon Ja
for Mother's daughter.

201
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:17,313
Anyway, it all worked out. Cheers.

202
00:12:17,313 --> 00:12:18,672
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

203
00:12:21,036 --> 00:12:22,445
Still, what should we do?

204
00:12:23,084 --> 00:12:25,443
I feel bad that I pulled out her hair
for nothing.

205
00:12:25,669 --> 00:12:27,277
I feel the same way.

206
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,856
I kept nitpicking everything,

207
00:12:29,856 --> 00:12:32,656
hoping he'd get fed up
and quit on his own.

208
00:12:34,133 --> 00:12:36,833
Honey, should we all just apologize?

209
00:12:36,989 --> 00:12:38,560
Apologize? How?

210
00:12:39,088 --> 00:12:40,555
Tomorrow,

211
00:12:40,555 --> 00:12:43,064
we could get some premium Korean beef,

212
00:12:43,475 --> 00:12:46,381
say we're visiting an employee,
who's like family,

213
00:12:46,381 --> 00:12:48,088
and then casually hand the beef over.

214
00:12:48,786 --> 00:12:52,051
My goodness, that's a wonderful idea.

215
00:12:52,739 --> 00:12:54,907
How are you so kind?

216
00:12:55,137 --> 00:12:56,907
Not everyone could do that.

217
00:12:57,200 --> 00:13:00,125
Seriously, what kind of CEO
personally buys beef and visits...

218
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:03,400
an employee's home just because
he gave his assistant a hard time?

219
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:06,720
Well, I suppose I do have that side to me.

220
00:13:13,339 --> 00:13:14,771
Let's stop holding hands now.

221
00:13:14,859 --> 00:13:16,523
What? Why?

222
00:13:16,523 --> 00:13:17,523
Just a little longer.

223
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:20,187
What if my family sees us?

224
00:13:20,409 --> 00:13:23,989
Are you planning to keep our relationship
a secret from them?

225
00:13:24,523 --> 00:13:26,544
Of course I want to tell them.

226
00:13:27,065 --> 00:13:30,093
But because of my brother,
everyone's already having a hard time.

227
00:13:30,952 --> 00:13:31,952
Later.

228
00:13:33,485 --> 00:13:35,271
Let go of my hand.

229
00:13:35,271 --> 00:13:37,171
Just a little longer. Five more steps.

230
00:13:37,171 --> 00:13:38,957
What are you doing?

231
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,433
Dad!

232
00:13:46,979 --> 00:13:47,979
What are you doing here at this hour?

233
00:13:48,539 --> 00:13:50,200
Did you just get back from your walk?

234
00:13:50,709 --> 00:13:51,709
Yeah.

235
00:13:52,091 --> 00:13:53,549
I took a walk around the neighborhood.

236
00:13:55,632 --> 00:13:58,952
There's something I'd like to tell you.
Actually, we...

237
00:13:58,952 --> 00:14:01,629
Dad, let's go inside. It's late.

238
00:14:02,681 --> 00:14:03,681
Eun Ae, you go in first.

239
00:14:04,633 --> 00:14:06,381
Team Manager Ko, I'd like a word with you.

240
00:14:06,872 --> 00:14:08,117
Yes, sir.

241
00:14:08,544 --> 00:14:09,544
Dad.

242
00:14:13,989 --> 00:14:15,115
I'm home.

243
00:14:15,485 --> 00:14:16,784
Hey, you're late.

244
00:14:17,547 --> 00:14:19,912
Yeah, our business trip ran long.

245
00:14:20,455 --> 00:14:22,528
- Are you studying?
- Yeah.

246
00:14:23,233 --> 00:14:25,953
I neglected it for a while
because of everything going on,

247
00:14:25,953 --> 00:14:27,053
so it's been rough.

248
00:14:27,629 --> 00:14:30,229
I guess that's why people say
there's a right time for studying.

249
00:14:31,306 --> 00:14:33,336
Didn't Team Manager Ko come with you?

250
00:14:33,724 --> 00:14:35,148
What? Right...

251
00:14:35,148 --> 00:14:36,763
He did.

252
00:14:37,125 --> 00:14:40,403
But we met Dad at the gate,
and they had something to talk about.

253
00:14:40,956 --> 00:14:42,623
What would your dad have to talk about
with Team Manager Ko?

254
00:14:43,325 --> 00:14:44,325
I don't know.

255
00:14:45,168 --> 00:14:46,168
Go upstairs and get some rest.

256
00:14:46,416 --> 00:14:47,747
Okay. Good luck with your studying.

257
00:14:52,258 --> 00:14:54,715
You turned down Eun Ae's confession,
saying you'd be leaving soon.

258
00:14:55,636 --> 00:14:56,531
What happened?

259
00:14:57,981 --> 00:15:00,141
So you heard. I'm sorry.

260
00:15:00,777 --> 00:15:03,595
I wasn't going to start something
I couldn't take responsibility for.

261
00:15:04,285 --> 00:15:06,944
But my feelings for Eun Ae...

262
00:15:07,225 --> 00:15:08,571
have grown too strong.

263
00:15:09,309 --> 00:15:10,342
What you're saying is,

264
00:15:10,961 --> 00:15:12,795
even though you know
you can't take responsibility,

265
00:15:13,633 --> 00:15:15,935
you're going to follow
your feelings anyway?

266
00:15:15,935 --> 00:15:17,861
No. That's absolutely not it.

267
00:15:18,020 --> 00:15:19,087
If that's not it,

268
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,427
does that mean you're going to stay
by Eun Ae's side...

269
00:15:22,128 --> 00:15:23,628
instead of leaving as planned?

270
00:15:24,616 --> 00:15:27,069
I haven't made a final decision
about that yet,

271
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:29,264
but both Eun Ae and I...

272
00:15:29,264 --> 00:15:31,339
plan to find an answer
that will make us both happy.

273
00:15:31,339 --> 00:15:33,235
Of course that's the right answer...

274
00:15:35,906 --> 00:15:37,573
but as Eun Ae's father,
I can't help but worry.

275
00:15:38,133 --> 00:15:41,533
Eun Ae seems to like you a lot,

276
00:15:42,541 --> 00:15:46,035
and I'm worried she might
end up getting hurt.

277
00:15:46,417 --> 00:15:49,576
I don't want Eun Ae to get hurt either.

278
00:15:50,444 --> 00:15:52,944
Please trust us and watch over us.

279
00:15:53,657 --> 00:15:56,657
I'll do everything I can
not to disappoint you.

280
00:16:03,973 --> 00:16:05,073
Are you done drawing?

281
00:16:13,581 --> 00:16:14,581
Cho Eun Nim.

282
00:16:15,196 --> 00:16:16,263
Forget Oh Hye Ji.

283
00:16:16,684 --> 00:16:18,784
Aren't you the one who needs an eye exam?

284
00:16:19,906 --> 00:16:22,473
How can that slick guy
possibly look handsome?

285
00:16:37,420 --> 00:16:39,387
Eun Ae, how do I look?

286
00:16:40,125 --> 00:16:41,125
What?

287
00:16:41,125 --> 00:16:44,139
I'm thinking about switching
from glasses to contacts.

288
00:16:44,324 --> 00:16:45,536
What? All of a sudden?

289
00:16:46,001 --> 00:16:47,601
You said contacts were uncomfortable.

290
00:16:47,709 --> 00:16:49,355
That was a long time ago.

291
00:16:49,585 --> 00:16:51,256
Do you know how good contacts are
these days?

292
00:16:51,533 --> 00:16:53,400
They're pretty. Bright and sparkly.

293
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:56,200
Your eyes were always
your prettiest feature.

294
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,200
Really?

295
00:16:59,321 --> 00:17:00,954
I'm pretty? Even to you?

296
00:17:01,344 --> 00:17:03,144
Why? Did someone tell you you're pretty?

297
00:17:03,144 --> 00:17:06,029
No, it's not that.

298
00:17:24,084 --> 00:17:25,084
Dad.

299
00:17:25,996 --> 00:17:26,996
In the end,

300
00:17:28,031 --> 00:17:29,757
I surrendered to that girl.

301
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:32,433
I'm very scared,

302
00:17:34,179 --> 00:17:35,600
but I'm going to be brave.

303
00:17:41,541 --> 00:17:43,187
Hello, big bro.

304
00:17:45,109 --> 00:17:48,507
What?
You confessed to the person you like?

305
00:17:49,433 --> 00:17:50,433
Yes.

306
00:17:50,633 --> 00:17:53,551
Just like you said, I want
to hold on tightly to this feeling...

307
00:17:53,551 --> 00:17:56,284
that may never come again in my life.

308
00:17:58,646 --> 00:18:01,046
Congratulations. You did the right thing.

309
00:18:01,046 --> 00:18:04,891
But when the time comes for me
to leave in a few months,

310
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:06,300
what do I do then?

311
00:18:07,381 --> 00:18:10,624
If you love each other,
couldn't you leave together?

312
00:18:11,401 --> 00:18:13,551
Her beloved family, her work,

313
00:18:13,551 --> 00:18:15,551
and everything else are here.

314
00:18:16,157 --> 00:18:18,829
Asking her to give all that up
and come with me...

315
00:18:18,829 --> 00:18:20,032
feels selfish.

316
00:18:21,621 --> 00:18:24,128
Why do you have to leave at all?

317
00:18:24,748 --> 00:18:27,491
This is also a place
where someone you love lives.

318
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,600
Isn't that reason enough to stay?

319
00:18:32,239 --> 00:18:35,136
You always come up
with such clear answers.

320
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:37,371
I'll keep that in mind.

321
00:18:38,668 --> 00:18:40,701
That's life.

322
00:18:41,664 --> 00:18:43,139
Other people's problems seem easy,

323
00:18:43,368 --> 00:18:45,135
but your own problems are always hard.

324
00:18:50,733 --> 00:18:53,312
Are you back from a walk, Father?

325
00:18:53,312 --> 00:18:55,483
Yes. Today I went all the way...

326
00:18:55,835 --> 00:18:57,300
to the spring up the hill.

327
00:18:58,125 --> 00:19:00,899
Going somewhere? It's almost lunchtime.

328
00:19:00,899 --> 00:19:02,712
Yes.
I'm stopping by the department store...

329
00:19:02,712 --> 00:19:04,200
and then heading over
to Seong Jun's house.

330
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,200
What?

331
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:06,833
Why are you suddenly going
to Mr. Cho's house?

332
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:09,269
Well, he's practically family.

333
00:19:09,269 --> 00:19:10,912
I thought I'd see how they're doing...

334
00:19:11,132 --> 00:19:12,819
and chat for a while.

335
00:19:16,496 --> 00:19:18,400
Is Su Jeong going too?

336
00:19:18,658 --> 00:19:21,224
Of course. We're always a package deal.

337
00:19:21,909 --> 00:19:24,168
But why are you wearing a scarf?

338
00:19:24,644 --> 00:19:25,744
Planning to tail someone?

339
00:19:26,304 --> 00:19:29,541
Well, just in case she grabs me
by the hair again.

340
00:19:30,152 --> 00:19:31,739
We'll get going, Mother.

341
00:19:32,723 --> 00:19:33,933
We might be late.

342
00:19:33,933 --> 00:19:37,115
It's been a while, so I thought I'd have
a drink and catch up with Seong Jun.

343
00:19:37,633 --> 00:19:39,600
- Have a good time.
- Yes.

344
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:48,700
You couldn't sell that thing
even at a junk shop.

345
00:19:48,700 --> 00:19:51,227
Why wear yourself out fixing it
first thing in the morning?

346
00:19:51,363 --> 00:19:52,551
What are you talking about?

347
00:19:52,551 --> 00:19:54,384
Just a little more work,
and it'll be good as new.

348
00:19:55,648 --> 00:19:58,541
I also like to fix most things myself,
but you're truly impressive.

349
00:19:59,061 --> 00:20:01,200
- This was the problem.
- Right here.

350
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,200
Yes.

351
00:20:04,712 --> 00:20:07,027
Here's some cold watermelon juice.
Please enjoy.

352
00:20:07,929 --> 00:20:09,723
There.

353
00:20:09,723 --> 00:20:12,023
Now all it needs is a little oil.

354
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:15,573
I'll take care
of the finishing touches perfectly.

355
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:17,485
Here, drink this first.

356
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:18,667
Thank you.

357
00:20:18,667 --> 00:20:20,075
Don't waste your effort.

358
00:20:20,321 --> 00:20:22,632
The last time we put our trust in that
and rode it downhill was just...

359
00:20:23,374 --> 00:20:25,440
Where did you two go on that bicycle?

360
00:20:26,141 --> 00:20:29,144
I was just showing him around town.

361
00:20:29,144 --> 00:20:30,251
We took a ride around the neighborhood.

362
00:20:33,204 --> 00:20:35,317
What? You're going somewhere?

363
00:20:35,633 --> 00:20:36,900
- Yes, Grandpa.
- Right.

364
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:39,733
Dad, Aunt Cho Rong, and I
are going on a picnic.

365
00:20:40,147 --> 00:20:41,502
A picnic with Cho Rong?

366
00:20:41,502 --> 00:20:44,016
Yes, I think Bit Na made plans with her.

367
00:20:44,367 --> 00:20:45,992
Bit Na kept begging her to go together.

368
00:20:46,433 --> 00:20:47,982
- We're heading out.
- See you later.

369
00:20:47,982 --> 00:20:49,877
- Okay.
- Have fun, Bit Na.

370
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:51,140
Big bro, have a wonderful time.

371
00:20:51,140 --> 00:20:52,140
You too, little bro.

372
00:20:53,336 --> 00:20:54,769
"Big bro," "little bro?"

373
00:20:56,193 --> 00:20:58,104
Bit Na seems much happier.

374
00:20:58,317 --> 00:20:59,317
She does.

375
00:20:59,844 --> 00:21:03,067
But it's strange
how she's suddenly acting completely fine.

376
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:09,500
You said it was just Bit Na,
and you're taking bindaetteok too?

377
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:11,933
Isn't this way too much food?

378
00:21:11,933 --> 00:21:13,442
Don't worry.

379
00:21:13,442 --> 00:21:14,565
We won't leave a thing behind.

380
00:21:14,565 --> 00:21:16,877
There are three mouths to feed. All set.

381
00:21:17,449 --> 00:21:18,449
Three mouths?

382
00:21:21,171 --> 00:21:23,661
You're going on the picnic too,
Eun Hyeong?

383
00:21:23,661 --> 00:21:25,563
Bit Na kept begging me.

384
00:21:25,925 --> 00:21:26,925
Bit Na, good job.

385
00:21:27,157 --> 00:21:28,917
Three people are more fun than two,
don't you think?

386
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:30,928
- Shall we go now?
- Yes, Auntie.

387
00:21:30,928 --> 00:21:32,273
See you later, Grandma.

388
00:21:32,273 --> 00:21:34,673
I packed you some gimbap too,
so have it for lunch.

389
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:35,904
Okay.

390
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:37,941
- See you later.
- See you later.

391
00:21:37,941 --> 00:21:40,656
All right, Bit Na. Have fun.

392
00:21:42,672 --> 00:21:44,944
Looks like Bit Na...

393
00:21:45,768 --> 00:21:49,035
reminds you of yourself
when you were little.

394
00:21:49,247 --> 00:21:52,787
No matter what, the best medicine
for Bit Na is still her mother.

395
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,300
This is the real estate office
run by Mr. Cho's wife?

396
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:02,100
Yeah. But honey, I'm nervous.

397
00:22:02,100 --> 00:22:03,700
What if the moment she sees me,

398
00:22:03,973 --> 00:22:05,540
she decides to get revenge
and grabs me by the hair?

399
00:22:07,257 --> 00:22:08,257
Honey.

400
00:22:08,655 --> 00:22:11,195
What do you think of Team Manager Ko?

401
00:22:12,514 --> 00:22:14,213
He's a genuinely good person.

402
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:18,277
Just look at how readily
he gave Eun Hyeong his room.

403
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:21,563
He's thoughtful and very warm-hearted.

404
00:22:22,264 --> 00:22:24,733
I was watching him earlier,
and he really looked like family.

405
00:22:30,229 --> 00:22:32,733
What brings you here?

406
00:22:32,884 --> 00:22:35,563
Well, looks like we found the right place.

407
00:22:35,940 --> 00:22:38,473
Honey, what are you doing?

408
00:22:40,060 --> 00:22:42,747
Hello, Mr. Cho, Ms. Kang Yeon Ja.

409
00:22:43,471 --> 00:22:44,471
Hello.

410
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:47,433
What brings you to our house this time?

411
00:22:48,385 --> 00:22:50,021
I'm here to apologize
for what happened that day.

412
00:22:50,633 --> 00:22:53,813
Your hair looked so shiny,
and I was curious...

413
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:57,328
how you take care of your cuticles,

414
00:22:57,661 --> 00:22:59,900
so I only meant to pull out one strand,
but...

415
00:22:59,900 --> 00:23:01,900
Mom, Dad, we're taking the bicycle
out for a test...

416
00:23:03,072 --> 00:23:04,181
Eun Ae, wait for me.

417
00:23:05,757 --> 00:23:07,235
- My goodness.
- Gyeol?

418
00:23:07,599 --> 00:23:08,733
What are you doing here?

419
00:23:09,100 --> 00:23:10,475
Father, Mother.

420
00:23:10,681 --> 00:23:11,681
My goodness.

421
00:23:12,194 --> 00:23:15,361
I heard you two were dating, but you've
practically set up house together now?

422
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:16,900
What?

423
00:23:18,507 --> 00:23:20,453
This is the house I moved into
after becoming independent.

424
00:23:20,728 --> 00:23:22,109
I'm sorry I didn't tell you sooner.

425
00:23:23,900 --> 00:23:24,900
Mr. Cho.

426
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:27,200
Then why didn't you tell me before?

427
00:23:27,868 --> 00:23:29,699
No, I asked him not to.

428
00:23:30,384 --> 00:23:32,651
It's not like you were
all that curious anyway.

429
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:34,389
Have a good talk before you leave.

430
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:35,800
Let's go, Eun Ae.

431
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:37,500
What? Okay.

432
00:23:46,193 --> 00:23:47,861
They seem really shocked.

433
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:49,700
Is it okay for us to just leave like this?

434
00:23:50,040 --> 00:23:52,341
It's fine. I'll explain later.

435
00:23:59,641 --> 00:24:00,641
Hello, Grandpa.

436
00:24:01,432 --> 00:24:02,432
What?

437
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:05,700
We do have time.

438
00:24:08,504 --> 00:24:11,125
But more importantly, why did you
come to our house without even calling?

439
00:24:12,023 --> 00:24:16,016
Come on. We're close enough
that we don't need to call ahead.

440
00:24:16,473 --> 00:24:18,107
We're practically family.

441
00:24:22,681 --> 00:24:23,881
Wouldn't you agree, Yeon Ja?

442
00:24:24,113 --> 00:24:27,488
I don't know. You are the boss,

443
00:24:28,639 --> 00:24:29,639
and he's the employee.

444
00:24:30,687 --> 00:24:31,853
Family? Please.

445
00:24:34,637 --> 00:24:36,789
So, what brings you here?

446
00:24:37,012 --> 00:24:39,413
Come on, why are you being like that?

447
00:24:40,013 --> 00:24:43,488
You used to come in and out of our house
all the time in high school.

448
00:24:43,915 --> 00:24:45,651
I thought we should visit more often,

449
00:24:45,939 --> 00:24:47,560
especially now that Gyeol lives here.

450
00:24:48,317 --> 00:24:52,461
Wait. What was that about earlier?

451
00:24:52,461 --> 00:24:55,200
Our daughter is dating Team Manager Ko?

452
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:56,200
My goodness.

453
00:24:56,628 --> 00:25:00,408
It's so obvious,
but I guess you really had no idea...

454
00:25:00,408 --> 00:25:01,608
that they like each other.

455
00:25:02,233 --> 00:25:04,700
The whole company's been talking about it.

456
00:25:07,147 --> 00:25:08,560
We'll talk about that later.

457
00:25:09,544 --> 00:25:12,000
So where's Gyeol's room?

458
00:25:12,157 --> 00:25:14,790
Looks like
there's only one room downstairs.

459
00:25:15,172 --> 00:25:17,037
The kids' rooms are upstairs.

460
00:25:17,349 --> 00:25:18,349
Goodness.

461
00:25:18,448 --> 00:25:20,909
No wonder they were bound to fall
for each other.

462
00:25:22,165 --> 00:25:23,365
Fall for each other? Well...

463
00:25:23,837 --> 00:25:26,197
"Love blossomed." "Romance bloomed."

464
00:25:26,197 --> 00:25:27,488
Something like that.

465
00:25:29,575 --> 00:25:31,507
Right, Yeon Ja. I asked about it...

466
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:34,672
because I wanted
to celebrate your birthday.

467
00:25:34,672 --> 00:25:36,560
But it turns out your birthday
already passed this year.

468
00:25:36,824 --> 00:25:37,824
It was 0204, right?

469
00:25:38,112 --> 00:25:40,944
I'll make sure to celebrate it next year.

470
00:25:41,733 --> 00:25:42,800
What? 0204?

471
00:25:43,460 --> 00:25:46,149
That's not actually my birthday.

472
00:25:47,300 --> 00:25:49,803
What? Then does that mean you have...

473
00:25:49,803 --> 00:25:51,368
a different birthday?

474
00:25:52,263 --> 00:25:54,200
When is it?

475
00:25:54,749 --> 00:25:58,411
I invited you two here...

476
00:25:59,031 --> 00:26:00,664
to evaluate the senior date course
we tried that day.

477
00:26:02,024 --> 00:26:04,589
I'd love to hear your honest feedback.

478
00:26:05,165 --> 00:26:07,265
Did Eun Ae go into the room
with your grandma...

479
00:26:07,728 --> 00:26:09,736
because she wanted to talk to her?

480
00:26:10,883 --> 00:26:13,133
Actually, Eun Ae has been developing...

481
00:26:13,133 --> 00:26:15,211
a people-finder app.

482
00:26:15,752 --> 00:26:17,352
It's still in the testing stage,

483
00:26:17,670 --> 00:26:20,637
but she wanted Grandma
to be the first person to try it.

484
00:26:20,781 --> 00:26:21,781
What?

485
00:26:21,849 --> 00:26:24,904
You knew Grandma was looking for someone?

486
00:26:25,264 --> 00:26:26,757
Yes, Grandpa.

487
00:26:27,725 --> 00:26:31,219
But may I ask who she's looking for?

488
00:26:33,312 --> 00:26:35,461
Your grandmother's daughter.

489
00:26:36,645 --> 00:26:37,645
What?

490
00:26:38,821 --> 00:26:41,803
Now all you have to do
is enter the person's name,

491
00:26:41,803 --> 00:26:44,133
appearance, and where you were separated.

492
00:26:44,133 --> 00:26:45,747
Fill out these.

493
00:26:45,747 --> 00:26:48,448
And if you have a photo or an item
that might help identify them,

494
00:26:48,448 --> 00:26:49,589
you can upload it too.

495
00:26:51,058 --> 00:26:53,825
My goodness, how thoughtful.

496
00:26:58,522 --> 00:26:59,522
- Wait.
- Yeah.

497
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:02,913
If 0204 isn't her real birthday,

498
00:27:02,913 --> 00:27:04,440
then this changes everything.

499
00:27:05,181 --> 00:27:07,181
Why wouldn't she tell us in the end?

500
00:27:07,181 --> 00:27:08,733
That's just how she is.

501
00:27:08,900 --> 00:27:09,900
You saw it earlier, didn't you?

502
00:27:10,166 --> 00:27:12,421
You said we're practically family,

503
00:27:12,421 --> 00:27:15,321
and she immediately said,
"Family? Please."

504
00:27:15,512 --> 00:27:16,612
Honestly.

505
00:27:16,612 --> 00:27:18,843
- Unbelievable.
- What a piece of work.

506
00:27:24,965 --> 00:27:25,965
Is this Mr. Ko Dae Chi's residence?

507
00:27:26,075 --> 00:27:27,675
Yes, I'm Ko Dae Chi.

508
00:27:27,883 --> 00:27:29,461
- Delivery.
- Delivery? What's this?

509
00:27:30,433 --> 00:27:31,433
Could I get your signature?

510
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:33,700
Sure, one moment.

511
00:27:36,033 --> 00:27:37,576
Thank you.

512
00:27:39,281 --> 00:27:40,493
Delivery? What delivery?

513
00:27:41,004 --> 00:27:42,704
- The DNA test results.
- What?

514
00:27:43,800 --> 00:27:45,000
Open it. Hurry.

515
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:46,000
Hurry.

516
00:27:55,400 --> 00:27:57,800
(Lee Yeong Hwa and Kang Yeon Ja
are biologically related.)

517
00:28:00,360 --> 00:28:01,393
What?

518
00:28:19,300 --> 00:28:20,700
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
